1
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:34,980
=Wonder Wall=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,910
= Episode 15 =

3
00:01:38,151 --> 00:01:40,700
(Bridgeway Financial)

4
00:01:40,760 --> 00:01:42,200
In April 2007,

5
00:01:42,920 --> 00:01:44,560
you dared fake bids

6
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:46,200
for a fire safety renovation.

7
00:01:46,560 --> 00:01:47,239
Every company involved

8
00:01:47,239 --> 00:01:48,040
was a shell company.

9
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:50,760
Your quotes were more than double

10
00:01:50,760 --> 00:01:51,879
the industry average.

11
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:53,920
You've got some serious nerve!

12
00:01:54,439 --> 00:01:55,680
In May 2010,

13
00:01:55,799 --> 00:01:57,560
you worked with Mingcheng Times

14
00:01:57,599 --> 00:01:58,560
and got the project payment

15
00:01:58,599 --> 00:01:59,879
six months early.

16
00:01:59,879 --> 00:02:00,519
But the project?

17
00:02:00,760 --> 00:02:01,840
Where is the project?

18
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:05,359
There's another folder

19
00:02:06,359 --> 00:02:07,760
containing 150 emails,

20
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:09,960
403 images in total.

21
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,719
All are evidence, Ms. Li.

22
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:13,000
What do you want?

23
00:02:13,439 --> 00:02:15,039
You see, the Unit 505,

24
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:16,080
you are the owner,

25
00:02:16,680 --> 00:02:17,680
So am I.

26
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:18,800
Oh, hang on.

27
00:02:18,919 --> 00:02:19,639
Don't hang up.

28
00:02:19,879 --> 00:02:21,479
Let me send you something.

29
00:02:31,439 --> 00:02:32,840
I'm sure

30
00:02:33,319 --> 00:02:34,879
you'll get my point, Ms. Li.

31
00:02:35,199 --> 00:02:36,319
I'm not asking much.

32
00:02:36,639 --> 00:02:37,400
Fifty-fifty.

33
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:38,560
Fair, right?

34
00:02:39,120 --> 00:02:39,719
No problem.

35
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:42,080
I'll pick the place.

36
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:43,240
You pick the time.

37
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:44,639
Let's talk.

38
00:02:45,039 --> 00:02:45,599
Yes.

39
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:47,199
We need to talk.

40
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:48,560
Otherwise, this stuff

41
00:02:48,560 --> 00:02:49,520
in my hand

42
00:02:49,719 --> 00:02:50,840
is too hot to keep.

43
00:03:11,319 --> 00:03:12,319
He's too greedy.

44
00:03:38,759 --> 00:03:39,960
What a dump.

45
00:03:40,439 --> 00:03:41,439
Not a single spot left.

46
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:00,800
What was she thinking,

47
00:04:00,960 --> 00:04:01,879
picking a place like this?

48
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:19,560
Here.

49
00:04:21,120 --> 00:04:21,920
Four more cups.

50
00:04:22,279 --> 00:04:23,000
No, no.

51
00:04:23,199 --> 00:04:23,879
No need.

52
00:04:25,639 --> 00:04:26,120
Ms. Li.

53
00:04:26,879 --> 00:04:28,040
I've already had so many.

54
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:29,439
I really can't drink more.

55
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:30,920
You can't

56
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:32,199
drink coffee like this.

57
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:33,519
It's not good

58
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:34,680
for your heart.

59
00:04:35,319 --> 00:04:35,879
Right.

60
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,240
I understand you've been in...

61
00:04:41,160 --> 00:04:43,399
in there in those years.

62
00:04:43,639 --> 00:04:45,959
Things outside have changed fast.

63
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:48,199
Let me catch you up.

64
00:04:48,319 --> 00:04:48,879
Nowadays,

65
00:04:48,879 --> 00:04:50,399
there are so many apps on your phone.

66
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:52,560
Just open a live stream,

67
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:54,680
I could spend

68
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:55,279
just a few money,

69
00:04:55,279 --> 00:04:56,040
and I can get some girl

70
00:04:56,040 --> 00:04:57,000
to dance for me all night.

71
00:04:57,720 --> 00:04:58,199
For real.

72
00:04:58,519 --> 00:04:59,759
So I've changed my mind.

73
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:01,279
Why get married?

74
00:05:02,800 --> 00:05:03,920
Speaking of marriage,

75
00:05:04,040 --> 00:05:05,720
you're my cautionary tale.

76
00:05:06,319 --> 00:05:07,879
Think about it. You and

77
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:09,319
the one who hanged himself

78
00:05:09,360 --> 00:05:10,839
share a bed but not a heart.

79
00:05:10,879 --> 00:05:12,079
And you still made it.

80
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:13,600
In all my years

81
00:05:13,639 --> 00:05:14,240
of doing business,

82
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:15,199
I've never seen

83
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:16,160
a married couple

84
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:17,920
hold onto evidence

85
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:19,600
against each other so completely.

86
00:05:20,639 --> 00:05:21,160
Respect.

87
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:23,199
Mr. Hong,

88
00:05:23,759 --> 00:05:24,759
you see people clearly.

89
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:26,600
Even without sleeping in the same bed,

90
00:05:26,839 --> 00:05:27,680
you've covered other's

91
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:28,759
million-plus hole.

92
00:05:30,240 --> 00:05:31,959
Ms. Li, you're making fun of me.

93
00:05:33,199 --> 00:05:34,600
I, Hong Jinkui,

94
00:05:34,720 --> 00:05:35,519
am a man of the earth.

95
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:36,480
Earth by the roadside.

96
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:38,000
People like me,

97
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:40,120
we always need a little water
to keep us going.

98
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:42,399
And water means money.

99
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:43,720
So I was thinking,

100
00:05:43,720 --> 00:05:45,560
If one day I got rich,

101
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:47,199
I'd buy a big cruise ship,

102
00:05:47,439 --> 00:05:48,920
just floating on the sea.

103
00:05:49,199 --> 00:05:50,720
If I feel like a swim,

104
00:05:50,759 --> 00:05:51,639
I'll jump in.

105
00:05:51,879 --> 00:05:52,879
If I don't,

106
00:05:53,439 --> 00:05:54,759
I'll stay on deck

107
00:05:54,759 --> 00:05:56,279
and stare at the sea.

108
00:05:56,639 --> 00:05:57,360
Mr. Hong.

109
00:05:57,720 --> 00:05:59,160
Money only counts
when it's in your hand.

110
00:06:01,319 --> 00:06:02,399
Set a time.

111
00:06:03,079 --> 00:06:04,120
I'll get Yu Ming out of the way.

112
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:07,199
That's more like it, Ms. Li.

113
00:06:07,959 --> 00:06:09,439
Let's pick an auspicious day.

114
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:22,000
Let me know the time.

115
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:37,519
This is so sudden.

116
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:38,960
We never expected this.

117
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:40,159
How could this happen?

118
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:41,639
How do you explain this?

119
00:08:43,679 --> 00:08:44,240
No idea.

120
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:45,879
When was the last maintenance check?

121
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:46,799
Yesterday.

122
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:48,879
We do a full maintenance check

123
00:08:48,879 --> 00:08:50,240
every year.

124
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:51,799
And weekly inspections.

125
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:53,200
Everything should be fine.

126
00:08:53,559 --> 00:08:54,399
Inspection records?

127
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:55,279
In the office.

128
00:08:55,559 --> 00:08:56,080
Get them.

129
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:56,639
Yes, sir.

130
00:09:08,919 --> 00:09:09,559
(Air-raid shelter)
Find anything?

131
00:09:09,679 --> 00:09:10,120
(Air-raid shelter)
Captain Guo.

132
00:09:10,919 --> 00:09:11,559
This smoke detector

133
00:09:11,559 --> 00:09:13,320
triggered the first alarm.

134
00:09:13,759 --> 00:09:14,960
No burn marks

135
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:16,360
at the scene.

136
00:09:28,960 --> 00:09:29,720
Any cameras here?

137
00:09:29,879 --> 00:09:31,679
No cameras in the fire stairs.

138
00:09:33,879 --> 00:09:34,840
Anything else?

139
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:35,840
Nothing yet.

140
00:09:37,399 --> 00:09:37,919
Hui.

141
00:09:38,279 --> 00:09:39,360
Review all footage

142
00:09:39,399 --> 00:09:40,120
from this building

143
00:09:40,240 --> 00:09:41,039
over the past few days.

144
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:42,840
Look for anyone suspicious.

145
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:44,240
Got it.

146
00:10:00,759 --> 00:10:01,519
Find it?

147
00:10:02,120 --> 00:10:02,679
Not yet.

148
00:10:04,679 --> 00:10:05,679
Check anywhere with water.

149
00:11:42,840 --> 00:11:43,960
Is this the only copy?

150
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:46,000
He's dead.

151
00:11:46,759 --> 00:11:47,720
Even if there's a backup,

152
00:11:48,679 --> 00:11:50,039
it won't threaten you.

153
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:54,080
In this world,

154
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:56,279
nothing is ever certain.

155
00:11:57,120 --> 00:11:57,519
Here.

156
00:11:58,840 --> 00:11:59,559
A toast.

157
00:12:03,480 --> 00:12:04,080
Cheers.

158
00:12:18,759 --> 00:12:20,279
There're only five people

159
00:12:20,279 --> 00:12:20,879
for the inspection.

160
00:12:21,080 --> 00:12:21,919
The one who tampered with it

161
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:22,879
wasn't one of them.

162
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:23,799
Also,

163
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:24,840
based on body shape,

164
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:26,360
the janitor

165
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:27,559
and the fire tech are likely

166
00:12:27,639 --> 00:12:28,440
the same person.

167
00:12:28,759 --> 00:12:29,600
Before Hong Jinkui

168
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:30,320
drove in,

169
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:31,720
he was hanging around the parking area.

170
00:12:36,559 --> 00:12:37,039
Zoom in.

171
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:45,679
Rum him.

172
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:46,840
Find out who he is.

173
00:12:48,240 --> 00:12:50,279
Around 10:40 this morning,

174
00:12:50,440 --> 00:12:51,399
an accident occurred

175
00:12:51,399 --> 00:12:52,840
in the parking garage
of Blue Ocean Tower

176
00:12:53,120 --> 00:12:54,399
in Yanhua District.

177
00:12:54,559 --> 00:12:56,600
A man surnamed Hong was killed.

178
00:12:56,840 --> 00:12:57,559
His identity

179
00:12:57,759 --> 00:12:58,840
is pending confirmation.

180
00:12:58,919 --> 00:12:59,759
Early signs point to

181
00:12:59,840 --> 00:13:01,840
fire equipment failure.

182
00:13:02,039 --> 00:13:03,720
(Parking Garage Accident)
The cause remains under investigation.

183
00:13:03,759 --> 00:13:05,360
(Parking Garage Accident)
The chubby hand, ring, watch...

184
00:13:05,399 --> 00:13:06,600
(Parking Garage Accident)
Looks like Hong Jinkui.

185
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:09,240
He's...

186
00:13:10,559 --> 00:13:11,320
dead?

187
00:13:13,240 --> 00:13:14,039
Tests found

188
00:13:14,120 --> 00:13:15,399
large amounts of sulfur dioxide

189
00:13:15,399 --> 00:13:16,519
on residue collected

190
00:13:16,519 --> 00:13:18,000
from the smoke director.

191
00:13:18,279 --> 00:13:19,240
So we can basically confirm

192
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:20,720
that it was caused

193
00:13:20,919 --> 00:13:22,600
by a sulfur smoke pellet.

194
00:13:22,679 --> 00:13:24,879
When burned,
it releases a large amount of smoke,

195
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:26,080
which triggered the detector.

196
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:26,879
That much smoke

197
00:13:26,879 --> 00:13:28,159
set off the alarm.

198
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:29,080
Smoke pellets?

199
00:13:29,320 --> 00:13:30,639
That's not common, is it?

200
00:13:31,440 --> 00:13:31,840
No.

201
00:13:32,320 --> 00:13:33,960
They're usually used on stage

202
00:13:33,960 --> 00:13:34,799
or on film sets

203
00:13:34,799 --> 00:13:35,639
to create

204
00:13:35,639 --> 00:13:36,480
a certain atmosphere.

205
00:13:37,159 --> 00:13:37,840
But,

206
00:13:38,080 --> 00:13:38,919
why would someone go

207
00:13:38,919 --> 00:13:40,120
go into the fire stairwell

208
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:41,759
of the parking garage

209
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:42,600
and burn

210
00:13:42,840 --> 00:13:43,720
a smoke pellet?

211
00:13:45,039 --> 00:13:46,120
The fire alarm

212
00:13:46,399 --> 00:13:47,480
was definitely staged.

213
00:13:48,720 --> 00:13:49,720
Hong Jinkui's death

214
00:13:50,320 --> 00:13:51,399
shouldn't be an accident.

215
00:13:52,120 --> 00:13:52,879
It's very likely

216
00:13:52,879 --> 00:13:54,039
that he was set up.

217
00:14:12,159 --> 00:14:12,759
Let's talk.

218
00:14:22,879 --> 00:14:23,720
You go ahead.

219
00:14:33,759 --> 00:14:34,759
Nice yard.

220
00:14:36,759 --> 00:14:38,039
But you're a young woman.

221
00:14:39,639 --> 00:14:40,639
Living in someone else's home

222
00:14:40,759 --> 00:14:41,799
isn't ideal.

223
00:14:45,720 --> 00:14:46,440
Come home.

224
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:48,320
I've already set up your room

225
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:49,360
exactly the way

226
00:14:50,480 --> 00:14:51,960
you liked it as a child.

227
00:14:52,679 --> 00:14:53,519
You already got

228
00:14:53,519 --> 00:14:54,240
what my dad left me.

229
00:14:55,240 --> 00:14:55,919
Why are you still here?

230
00:15:00,679 --> 00:15:01,200
Nuo.

231
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:02,840
Have you ever wondered

232
00:15:03,320 --> 00:15:04,159
why the thing

233
00:15:04,159 --> 00:15:05,240
you fought so hard for,

234
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:07,360
I got

235
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:08,519
so easily?

236
00:15:10,159 --> 00:15:11,399
Because I knew your father.

237
00:15:12,080 --> 00:15:13,159
All his scheming,

238
00:15:13,159 --> 00:15:14,000
to me,

239
00:15:15,120 --> 00:15:16,200
was just childish and ridiculous.

240
00:15:17,120 --> 00:15:17,960
You understand?

241
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:19,919
Ridiculous.

242
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:24,120
Things have already blown up.

243
00:15:24,519 --> 00:15:26,080
We need a solution.

244
00:15:26,440 --> 00:15:27,879
Or we're finished.

245
00:15:30,960 --> 00:15:32,000
What do you suggest?

246
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:34,919
You're asking me?

247
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:38,240
You're the one behind all this.

248
00:15:40,120 --> 00:15:41,679
Someone has to take the fall.

249
00:15:43,080 --> 00:15:44,320
It's the only way.

250
00:15:45,919 --> 00:15:46,720
What are you planning?

251
00:15:49,639 --> 00:15:50,320
So you took the money

252
00:15:50,320 --> 00:15:51,360
and let him take the blame

253
00:15:52,559 --> 00:15:53,399
Isn't that ridiculous?

254
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:56,840
Don't you feel guilty at all?

255
00:15:59,639 --> 00:16:00,399
Five years.

256
00:16:03,240 --> 00:16:04,039
Some things should be

257
00:16:04,679 --> 00:16:05,360
left behind.

258
00:16:05,720 --> 00:16:07,080
Not for me. Never.

259
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:14,080
You got what you wanted.

260
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:16,679
Don't come looking for me again.

261
00:16:17,960 --> 00:16:18,720
Take care of yourself.

262
00:16:21,759 --> 00:16:22,480
I only wanted

263
00:16:22,519 --> 00:16:23,519
to be a good mother.

264
00:16:24,240 --> 00:16:25,240
Give me a chance.

265
00:16:26,320 --> 00:16:27,000
Just one.

266
00:16:27,480 --> 00:16:29,000
All the pressure I put on you,

267
00:16:29,159 --> 00:16:30,799
it was only
because I wanted you to be better.

268
00:16:31,279 --> 00:16:32,879
But now I know I was wrong.

269
00:16:33,519 --> 00:16:34,799
Can you forgive me?

270
00:16:35,240 --> 00:16:37,240
I really can be a good mother.

271
00:16:39,240 --> 00:16:39,879
You don't even know

272
00:16:39,879 --> 00:16:40,919
how to be a mother.

273
00:16:53,559 --> 00:16:54,360
One more thing.

274
00:16:55,799 --> 00:16:57,360
I never liked that room.
Not even as a child.

275
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:13,480
This is good.

276
00:17:14,039 --> 00:17:14,680
Another bowl.

277
00:17:16,759 --> 00:17:18,240
You've had three already.

278
00:17:18,440 --> 00:17:19,160
No more.

279
00:17:19,799 --> 00:17:21,000
You'll get bloated.

280
00:17:21,319 --> 00:17:22,640
She's still growing.

281
00:17:23,160 --> 00:17:23,799
It's fine.

282
00:17:24,039 --> 00:17:24,799
I'll get you some.

283
00:17:26,799 --> 00:17:28,559
Don't spoil her.

284
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:32,119
This kid has no self-control.

285
00:17:32,839 --> 00:17:34,880
A good appetite keeps sickness away.

286
00:17:36,119 --> 00:17:37,039
My little girl

287
00:17:37,279 --> 00:17:38,359
doesn't eat well.

288
00:17:38,599 --> 00:17:40,359
She's always catching colds.

289
00:17:40,599 --> 00:17:41,480
I'd be happy

290
00:17:41,480 --> 00:17:42,599
if she could eat and drink

291
00:17:42,799 --> 00:17:43,880
like Wenwen.

292
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:44,920
Healthy and strong.

293
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:45,880
That's all I want.

294
00:17:48,119 --> 00:17:48,599
Go ahead.

295
00:17:48,799 --> 00:17:49,319
Thanks.

296
00:17:50,119 --> 00:17:51,079
Don't have too much.

297
00:17:52,559 --> 00:17:52,920
It's fine.

298
00:17:52,920 --> 00:17:53,480
Jiang,

299
00:17:53,960 --> 00:17:55,680
you always talk about your daughter.

300
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:57,039
I don't knew

301
00:17:57,039 --> 00:17:58,440
what to get for her.

302
00:17:58,960 --> 00:18:00,720
I noticed you always wear

303
00:18:00,839 --> 00:18:02,240
a hair clip here.

304
00:18:03,039 --> 00:18:04,519
Like a keepsake.

305
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:06,920
So I bought her some hair clips.

306
00:18:07,400 --> 00:18:08,720
Look. Do you like them?

307
00:18:09,640 --> 00:18:10,960
I thought you would.

308
00:18:11,960 --> 00:18:12,720
These two

309
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,160
were picked by Wenwen.

310
00:18:15,359 --> 00:18:16,480
She usually spends

311
00:18:16,640 --> 00:18:18,519
all her allowance on snacks.

312
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:20,119
She's being thoughtful this time.

313
00:18:20,279 --> 00:18:21,079
Guess she's growing up.

314
00:18:30,240 --> 00:18:31,119
You don't like them?

315
00:18:33,079 --> 00:18:34,079
No, I do.

316
00:18:34,279 --> 00:18:34,839
I do.

317
00:18:35,160 --> 00:18:37,000
My hands are greasy.

318
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:38,279
I'll go wash up.

319
00:18:38,279 --> 00:18:39,079
Sure.

320
00:19:32,599 --> 00:19:33,599
How was your checkup

321
00:19:35,480 --> 00:19:36,519
last week?

322
00:19:40,400 --> 00:19:41,839
Let me tell you some good news.

323
00:19:42,200 --> 00:19:43,359
My health is a mess.

324
00:19:44,400 --> 00:19:46,759
High blood pressure.
I could have a stroke.

325
00:19:47,359 --> 00:19:49,759
High blood sugar.
My feet could rot.

326
00:19:50,440 --> 00:19:51,119
And something else

327
00:19:51,119 --> 00:19:52,279
in my blood was way too high.

328
00:19:52,279 --> 00:19:52,839
Can't remember.

329
00:19:52,839 --> 00:19:54,000
Anyway, it'll ruin my kidneys.

330
00:19:54,799 --> 00:19:55,680
I don't have long.

331
00:19:55,759 --> 00:19:56,880
I'll be dead soon.

332
00:20:01,240 --> 00:20:02,599
You need to control your sugar intake.

333
00:20:05,079 --> 00:20:06,880
Don't skip your blood pressure meds.

334
00:20:07,599 --> 00:20:08,720
You should also

335
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:10,000
monitor it regularly.

336
00:20:11,119 --> 00:20:11,680
Still acting?

337
00:20:12,799 --> 00:20:13,640
Go on.

338
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:15,440
Keep acting.

339
00:20:16,079 --> 00:20:17,000
If you can

340
00:20:17,599 --> 00:20:19,400
squeeze out a few tears,

341
00:20:19,960 --> 00:20:20,960
that'd make it perfect.

342
00:20:35,799 --> 00:20:36,400
Lanying.

343
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:39,240
All these years,

344
00:20:40,960 --> 00:20:42,440
I've neglected too much.

345
00:20:44,640 --> 00:20:46,359
I never gave you an explanation.

346
00:20:47,839 --> 00:20:48,880
Never made it up to you.

347
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:53,400
It's on me for not being around.

348
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:55,440
You suffered

349
00:20:57,039 --> 00:20:58,319
way too much.

350
00:21:02,920 --> 00:21:03,799
I'm sorry.

351
00:21:26,039 --> 00:21:27,200
Sorry?

352
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:31,160
A simple sorry

353
00:21:33,799 --> 00:21:34,839
and that's it?

354
00:21:46,640 --> 00:21:48,319
Don't give me that.

355
00:21:49,319 --> 00:21:49,880
You!

356
00:21:50,119 --> 00:21:51,759
You're so selfish.

357
00:21:52,480 --> 00:21:53,720
When Feng died,

358
00:21:53,799 --> 00:21:54,960
you said nothing.

359
00:21:55,559 --> 00:21:56,759
Not a word.

360
00:21:56,960 --> 00:21:58,519
Not a single tear.

361
00:21:59,160 --> 00:22:00,799
You're selfish.

362
00:22:01,240 --> 00:22:02,200
In your heart,

363
00:22:02,200 --> 00:22:03,519
You've never cared about us.

364
00:22:03,880 --> 00:22:05,759
You don't even see us.

365
00:22:21,400 --> 00:22:22,160
Apples?

366
00:22:23,440 --> 00:22:24,960
Do you think I've never had apples?

367
00:22:26,160 --> 00:22:27,519
Always buying random stuff.

368
00:22:28,158 --> 00:22:29,760
(Glucose Meter)

369
00:22:46,520 --> 00:22:49,962
(Glucose Meter,
Electronic Blood Pressure Monitor)

370
00:23:31,480 --> 00:23:32,400
Is that Hong Jinkui?

371
00:23:34,759 --> 00:23:35,680
That's him.

372
00:23:40,680 --> 00:23:41,559
His death has to be

373
00:23:41,559 --> 00:23:42,759
connected to that money.

374
00:23:45,440 --> 00:23:46,440
Don't try to fool me

375
00:23:46,440 --> 00:23:47,680
with something cheap.

376
00:23:47,799 --> 00:23:48,759
Listen, Yu Ming.

377
00:23:48,880 --> 00:23:50,119
Your good days are over.

378
00:23:50,279 --> 00:23:50,759
It's your fate

379
00:23:50,759 --> 00:23:51,920
to fight over scraps.

380
00:23:53,079 --> 00:23:56,359
Once I'd fight for every coin.

381
00:23:56,720 --> 00:23:59,440
Now my heart is wide as ocean.

382
00:24:00,079 --> 00:24:01,799
Small money like this

383
00:24:02,440 --> 00:24:06,839
no longer catch my eye.

384
00:24:10,400 --> 00:24:12,000
At 2:32 a.m.,

385
00:24:12,680 --> 00:24:13,519
Hong Jinkui

386
00:24:13,640 --> 00:24:15,119
send me this last message.

387
00:24:15,279 --> 00:24:17,160
Then there is nothing.

388
00:24:17,680 --> 00:24:18,599
"Small money like this

389
00:24:18,599 --> 00:24:19,839
no longer catch my eye"?

390
00:24:19,920 --> 00:24:21,160
What did he mean?

391
00:24:21,680 --> 00:24:23,319
He wanted totake all 60 million himself.

392
00:24:26,119 --> 00:24:27,119
That's what I think.

393
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:29,240
Part of that 60 million
belongs to Li Jin, right?

394
00:24:29,880 --> 00:24:30,839
Li Jin did it.

395
00:24:30,880 --> 00:24:31,880
She's the one who killed him.

396
00:24:32,240 --> 00:24:33,240
I agree.

397
00:24:33,480 --> 00:24:34,440
That's terrifying.

398
00:24:34,559 --> 00:24:35,319
It's cold-blooded.

399
00:24:35,480 --> 00:24:36,319
The valve shot

400
00:24:36,319 --> 00:24:37,000
into his head.

401
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:37,640
It's terrifying.

402
00:24:44,480 --> 00:24:46,240
If she could kill Hong Jinkui,

403
00:24:46,440 --> 00:24:47,359
she could kill us too.

404
00:24:47,599 --> 00:24:48,599
Hong Jinkui is one person.

405
00:24:48,640 --> 00:24:49,440
We are a whole family.

406
00:24:49,640 --> 00:24:51,319
Either she kills us all,

407
00:24:51,400 --> 00:24:52,119
or she picks us off

408
00:24:52,160 --> 00:24:53,400
one by one.

409
00:24:53,440 --> 00:24:54,359
If she doesn't die,

410
00:24:55,799 --> 00:24:57,160
we'll die.

411
00:24:57,440 --> 00:24:59,039
So what's our move?

412
00:25:06,759 --> 00:25:08,119
Give her back the money.

413
00:25:08,240 --> 00:25:08,920
Give her the house.

414
00:25:08,920 --> 00:25:09,440
Give her all.

415
00:25:09,440 --> 00:25:09,920
All.

416
00:25:10,400 --> 00:25:10,960
Maybe we can

417
00:25:10,960 --> 00:25:12,119
try to keep the house money.

418
00:25:26,480 --> 00:25:27,200
I'm leaving.

419
00:25:27,559 --> 00:25:28,720
Fan Meijuan's waiting for me.

420
00:25:30,480 --> 00:25:31,599
Drink the soup.

421
00:25:31,720 --> 00:25:32,920
It's good for your injury.

422
00:25:34,119 --> 00:25:34,839
I've been chasing

423
00:25:34,839 --> 00:25:35,799
this money for years.

424
00:25:35,960 --> 00:25:37,079
I'm so close now.

425
00:25:37,279 --> 00:25:38,759
Why is this last step so hard?

426
00:25:38,920 --> 00:25:39,960
Be patient.

427
00:25:40,079 --> 00:25:41,240
Yu Ming and his wife

428
00:25:41,559 --> 00:25:42,240
are slippery.

429
00:25:42,440 --> 00:25:43,319
They're hard to track.

430
00:25:43,400 --> 00:25:44,200
Hard to track?

431
00:25:44,839 --> 00:25:45,799
I think you're addicted

432
00:25:45,799 --> 00:25:46,640
to taking care of people.

433
00:25:47,240 --> 00:25:48,200
You are crazy.

434
00:25:49,000 --> 00:25:50,240
What's wrong with you?

435
00:25:50,440 --> 00:25:51,200
I am crazy.

436
00:25:51,400 --> 00:25:53,119
We're surrounded now.

437
00:25:53,240 --> 00:25:54,480
Everyone's after the money.

438
00:25:54,759 --> 00:25:55,759
And we can't cross that fish woman.

439
00:25:56,160 --> 00:25:56,880
So what do we do?

440
00:26:00,039 --> 00:26:01,200
Get the old woman and the kid

441
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:01,960
out for me.

442
00:26:06,400 --> 00:26:07,119
For what?

443
00:26:07,440 --> 00:26:08,359
Have you lost your mind?

444
00:26:08,559 --> 00:26:09,519
One life on your hands

445
00:26:09,519 --> 00:26:10,400
isn't enough?

446
00:26:10,559 --> 00:26:11,599
No, it isn't.

447
00:26:11,680 --> 00:26:12,839
What's not enough is time.

448
00:26:16,759 --> 00:26:18,200
But you can't touch them.

449
00:26:21,119 --> 00:26:22,680
They're not like Hu Deshuai.

450
00:26:22,839 --> 00:26:24,440
No. You think they're different.

451
00:26:24,559 --> 00:26:26,079
You've started
treating them like family.

452
00:26:26,480 --> 00:26:27,240
Want to see Yao?

453
00:26:28,759 --> 00:26:29,480
Do this,

454
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:30,880
and I'll take you to her.

455
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:36,240
You found her?

456
00:26:36,720 --> 00:26:37,279
I did.

457
00:26:37,640 --> 00:26:38,960
I know what she eats every day,

458
00:26:39,000 --> 00:26:39,880
her school schedule.

459
00:26:40,839 --> 00:26:42,319
Why didn't you tell me?

460
00:26:46,920 --> 00:26:47,720
I see now.

461
00:26:49,319 --> 00:26:50,880
You're using my daughter

462
00:26:52,000 --> 00:26:53,079
to threaten me.

463
00:26:54,440 --> 00:26:55,799
Not a threat. A reminder.

464
00:26:56,039 --> 00:26:56,880
Wake up.

465
00:27:03,966 --> 00:27:05,779
(Hero of Wang Village)

466
00:27:12,480 --> 00:27:13,279
Mr. Yu!

467
00:27:13,480 --> 00:27:14,880
Mr. Yu, look!

468
00:27:15,400 --> 00:27:16,880
We're handing out the money!

469
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:18,000
You earned this money.

470
00:27:18,160 --> 00:27:18,799
Enjoy it.

471
00:27:19,079 --> 00:27:19,960
Thanks!

472
00:27:20,319 --> 00:27:21,079
Zhu!

473
00:27:21,279 --> 00:27:21,839
Mr. Yu!

474
00:27:23,039 --> 00:27:23,680
Mr. Yu!

475
00:27:23,920 --> 00:27:24,400
Mr. Yu!

476
00:27:24,440 --> 00:27:25,000
Mr. Yu!

477
00:27:25,079 --> 00:27:25,599
I...

478
00:27:25,880 --> 00:27:26,720
About that...

479
00:27:26,759 --> 00:27:28,200
That phone...

480
00:27:28,400 --> 00:27:29,279
You said

481
00:27:29,359 --> 00:27:30,119
Recording

482
00:27:30,319 --> 00:27:31,400
It's recording there.

483
00:27:31,839 --> 00:27:33,079
We sign here.

484
00:27:33,200 --> 00:27:34,559
Leave thumbprint.

485
00:27:34,640 --> 00:27:36,319
Let me show Mr. Yu our new truck.

486
00:27:36,440 --> 00:27:37,279
Go. Go ahead.

487
00:27:38,319 --> 00:27:39,720
Let me show you our new truck.

488
00:27:40,119 --> 00:27:40,720
Mr. Yu,

489
00:27:41,160 --> 00:27:41,799
Take a look.

490
00:27:42,680 --> 00:27:43,559
This is our new truck.

491
00:27:43,759 --> 00:27:44,720
Brand-new box truck.

492
00:27:45,279 --> 00:27:46,440
We're getting into freight now.

493
00:27:46,759 --> 00:27:47,599
Good. Keep it up.

494
00:27:47,960 --> 00:27:48,359
San,

495
00:27:48,680 --> 00:27:50,039
I have things to do. Gotta go.

496
00:27:50,039 --> 00:27:50,640
Sure, sure.

497
00:27:50,839 --> 00:27:51,759
Take care, Mr. Yu.

498
00:27:52,240 --> 00:27:53,000
Right here.

499
00:27:54,160 --> 00:27:54,680
Me.

500
00:27:54,799 --> 00:27:55,480
7,900.

501
00:27:55,559 --> 00:27:56,160
Here.

502
00:27:56,160 --> 00:27:57,359
Zhang Zhize. 7,900.

503
00:27:57,359 --> 00:27:58,359
This is me.

504
00:27:59,759 --> 00:28:01,039
Have a cigarette.

505
00:28:01,039 --> 00:28:02,559
Cigarette won't get you more money.

506
00:28:02,720 --> 00:28:03,319
Here, take one.

507
00:28:03,319 --> 00:28:04,119
Here you are.

508
00:28:04,240 --> 00:28:04,880
This is my ID.

509
00:28:04,920 --> 00:28:06,000
Next. Next.

510
00:28:07,279 --> 00:28:08,160
Thank you.

511
00:28:09,720 --> 00:28:10,119
Told you.

512
00:28:10,160 --> 00:28:11,359
We won't hold up your money.

513
00:28:12,079 --> 00:28:13,599
No need.

514
00:28:13,680 --> 00:28:14,240
Have a smoke.

515
00:28:16,119 --> 00:28:16,680
Count it.

516
00:28:16,839 --> 00:28:17,799
Count your money.

517
00:28:17,920 --> 00:28:18,480
Thanks to you.

518
00:28:18,480 --> 00:28:19,119
No worries.

519
00:28:19,200 --> 00:28:19,559
Thank you.

520
00:28:19,559 --> 00:28:19,960
See you.

521
00:28:20,720 --> 00:28:21,319
No problem.

522
00:28:22,440 --> 00:28:23,519
Watch it. Don't push.

523
00:28:23,799 --> 00:28:25,200
Here are cash.

524
00:28:25,359 --> 00:28:26,160
Easy. Easy.

525
00:28:26,200 --> 00:28:26,720
Okay.

526
00:28:27,680 --> 00:28:28,160
Is it good?

527
00:28:28,519 --> 00:28:29,000
Not bad.

528
00:28:29,400 --> 00:28:30,119
It's you?

529
00:28:31,480 --> 00:28:32,400
Your great-grandma got

530
00:28:32,440 --> 00:28:33,359
even more people than this.

531
00:28:34,559 --> 00:28:35,400
She hasn't spoken

532
00:28:35,599 --> 00:28:36,799
for years.

533
00:28:37,000 --> 00:28:37,680
Yet she's still

534
00:28:37,720 --> 00:28:38,359
telling fortunes.

535
00:28:38,359 --> 00:28:38,640
Come on.

536
00:28:38,839 --> 00:28:39,720
Pretty amazing.

537
00:28:40,799 --> 00:28:43,039
My great-grandma's line has the gift.

538
00:28:43,519 --> 00:28:44,440
Sharper with age.

539
00:28:45,279 --> 00:28:45,880
Impressive.

540
00:28:47,200 --> 00:28:47,920
Great-grandma,

541
00:28:48,200 --> 00:28:49,319
why won't my hens

542
00:28:49,319 --> 00:28:50,519
lay eggs?

543
00:28:50,640 --> 00:28:51,720
Your hens won't lay eggs,

544
00:28:51,759 --> 00:28:52,480
and you're asking her?

545
00:28:52,480 --> 00:28:52,839
Exactly.

546
00:28:52,839 --> 00:28:53,920
Ask your hens.

547
00:28:54,480 --> 00:28:55,000
Great-grandma,

548
00:28:55,160 --> 00:28:56,000
is my daughter-in-law

549
00:28:56,119 --> 00:28:57,200
seeing someone else?

550
00:28:57,319 --> 00:28:58,359
She's always out.

551
00:28:58,640 --> 00:28:59,640
The things you ask...

552
00:29:00,440 --> 00:29:01,079
Great-grandma!

553
00:29:01,200 --> 00:29:02,880
Do you think my marriage proposal

554
00:29:02,920 --> 00:29:03,640
will work out?

555
00:29:04,799 --> 00:29:05,720
What does that mean?

556
00:29:06,279 --> 00:29:07,319
One tap means yes.

557
00:29:07,319 --> 00:29:08,519
Two taps mean no.

558
00:29:08,799 --> 00:29:09,720
Then it's a yes!

559
00:29:10,079 --> 00:29:10,799
Thank you.

560
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:11,599
Thank you.

561
00:29:11,799 --> 00:29:12,279
Great-grandma,

562
00:29:12,480 --> 00:29:15,200
my son's been trying to
get into college for three years.

563
00:29:15,200 --> 00:29:16,200
Will he make it?

564
00:29:16,200 --> 00:29:16,799
If not,

565
00:29:16,799 --> 00:29:18,000
we'll go broke.

566
00:29:21,200 --> 00:29:22,000
Not likely.

567
00:29:22,039 --> 00:29:23,640
What... what's not likely?

568
00:29:23,759 --> 00:29:24,279
Great-grandma,

569
00:29:25,079 --> 00:29:26,640
my mom's still sick.

570
00:29:26,720 --> 00:29:28,480
Do you think she'll
make it through the year?

571
00:29:28,920 --> 00:29:29,359
Great-grandma.

572
00:29:29,559 --> 00:29:30,039
Great-grandma.

573
00:29:30,119 --> 00:29:30,559
Great-grandma.

574
00:29:30,680 --> 00:29:31,759
Don't sleep!

575
00:30:02,640 --> 00:30:03,799
That's all you're eating?

576
00:30:03,960 --> 00:30:05,400
You can't just eat

577
00:30:05,400 --> 00:30:06,519
whatever's easy.

578
00:30:06,519 --> 00:30:07,680
There's no nutrition in it.

579
00:30:09,960 --> 00:30:11,480
These are from the best
free-range chicken

580
00:30:11,559 --> 00:30:12,640
the best,

581
00:30:12,720 --> 00:30:13,880
most nutritious eggs.

582
00:30:14,200 --> 00:30:15,920
Boil them every day.

583
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:17,200
Don't boil them for too long,

584
00:30:17,240 --> 00:30:18,480
or the nutrients leak out.

585
00:30:18,559 --> 00:30:19,720
Two eggs a day.

586
00:30:22,359 --> 00:30:22,799
Okay.

587
00:30:23,960 --> 00:30:25,319
This morning,

588
00:30:25,640 --> 00:30:26,759
I bought some pig trotters

589
00:30:26,799 --> 00:30:27,960
from Old Yao's place.

590
00:30:28,400 --> 00:30:30,119
I stewed them for three hours.

591
00:30:30,640 --> 00:30:31,759
Didn't Fan Meijuan

592
00:30:31,799 --> 00:30:32,960
take a bad fall?

593
00:30:33,240 --> 00:30:34,559
I haven't even gone to see her yet.

594
00:30:35,359 --> 00:30:36,279
Whatever happened,

595
00:30:36,440 --> 00:30:37,480
we're still family.

596
00:30:37,839 --> 00:30:39,079
I'll bring some over later.

597
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:46,920
Honestly,

598
00:30:47,200 --> 00:30:47,960
why eat that?

599
00:30:47,960 --> 00:30:49,079
There is no nutrition in it.

600
00:30:49,960 --> 00:30:51,319
Anyway, I made a lot.

601
00:30:51,319 --> 00:30:52,240
Take your chopsticks.

602
00:31:01,839 --> 00:31:02,799
Drink it while it's hot.

603
00:31:15,319 --> 00:31:16,400
Have some more.

604
00:31:20,960 --> 00:31:21,839
Would you

605
00:31:22,039 --> 00:31:23,640
come with me to see Fan Meijuan?

606
00:31:27,480 --> 00:31:28,000
Okay.

607
00:31:40,502 --> 00:31:42,707
(Zhan: I'll be right there.
Bring them out.)

608
00:31:42,839 --> 00:31:44,799
Your mom was always
good at analyzing this.

609
00:31:45,160 --> 00:31:46,160
She always tells me

610
00:31:46,680 --> 00:31:47,839
before you make a move,

611
00:31:48,359 --> 00:31:49,400
once you mention

612
00:31:49,400 --> 00:31:51,240
having kids, parents, the elderly,

613
00:31:51,319 --> 00:31:52,559
that person's going down first.

614
00:31:52,599 --> 00:31:53,960
He wasn't the first to go.

615
00:31:53,960 --> 00:31:54,640
She was.

616
00:31:55,200 --> 00:31:56,240
Here they come.

617
00:31:56,599 --> 00:31:57,559
Oh no!

618
00:32:09,200 --> 00:32:09,720
Ma'am,

619
00:32:10,079 --> 00:32:10,839
the other day

620
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:12,400
I found an amazing

621
00:32:12,400 --> 00:32:13,119
Sichuan restaurant.

622
00:32:13,319 --> 00:32:14,160
So spicy,

623
00:32:14,200 --> 00:32:15,200
you'll eat three bowls of rice.

624
00:32:15,400 --> 00:32:16,640
They even have torch cakes.

625
00:32:16,960 --> 00:32:17,839
What's a torch cake?

626
00:32:18,319 --> 00:32:20,200
It's a stick

627
00:32:20,279 --> 00:32:22,880
that's crispy, fragrant, and crunchy,

628
00:32:22,880 --> 00:32:24,400
dipped in sugar and fried.

629
00:32:24,400 --> 00:32:25,240
After frying,

630
00:32:25,240 --> 00:32:26,240
dip it in sticky rice cake.

631
00:32:26,720 --> 00:32:28,079
Sweet, crispy and chewy.

632
00:32:28,599 --> 00:32:29,680
I want a torch cake.

633
00:32:30,319 --> 00:32:31,680
Forget that.

634
00:32:32,640 --> 00:32:34,319
I will make you sweet rice cake.

635
00:32:34,599 --> 00:32:35,720
You've never had it.

636
00:32:35,759 --> 00:32:36,680
It's delicious.

637
00:32:39,960 --> 00:32:40,599
Ma'am,

638
00:32:41,039 --> 00:32:42,720
if Wenwen wants it, let's go there.

639
00:32:42,759 --> 00:32:43,400
You've taken

640
00:32:43,400 --> 00:32:44,640
such good care of me.

641
00:32:44,720 --> 00:32:45,880
I haven't thanked you properly.

642
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:46,839
Let me treat you.

643
00:32:47,880 --> 00:32:49,200
Please, Grandma?

644
00:32:49,200 --> 00:32:49,799
Let's go.

645
00:32:50,240 --> 00:32:51,079
Alright.

646
00:32:51,279 --> 00:32:52,480
Let's go then.

647
00:32:52,880 --> 00:32:53,960
I'll get a taxi now.

648
00:32:54,359 --> 00:32:54,799
Okay.

649
00:33:00,559 --> 00:33:01,119
We're here.

650
00:33:04,160 --> 00:33:05,559
This car's worse than my dad's.

651
00:33:05,920 --> 00:33:06,599
Sorry.

652
00:33:07,200 --> 00:33:08,440
This was cheaper.

653
00:33:08,720 --> 00:33:09,759
As long as it gets us here.

654
00:33:10,319 --> 00:33:10,880
Careful.

655
00:33:11,000 --> 00:33:11,880
Cheap is good.

656
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:12,920
Hold on tight.

657
00:33:19,400 --> 00:33:19,960
Let's go.

658
00:33:26,960 --> 00:33:29,200
Driving a car with a helmet on?

659
00:33:34,559 --> 00:33:35,119
Good grief.

660
00:33:35,720 --> 00:33:36,839
Never seen that before.

661
00:33:39,680 --> 00:33:41,640
Why are you wearing a helmet?

662
00:33:43,640 --> 00:33:44,400
It's safer this way.

663
00:33:46,880 --> 00:33:47,359
Okay.

664
00:33:47,680 --> 00:33:48,240
Ma'ma,

665
00:33:48,319 --> 00:33:49,519
I just made some fruit tea.

666
00:33:50,079 --> 00:33:51,000
No sugar.

667
00:33:51,720 --> 00:33:52,480
Look at you.

668
00:33:52,799 --> 00:33:53,799
Thanks.

669
00:33:54,000 --> 00:33:55,519
For Wenwen, it's grape oolong.

670
00:33:55,759 --> 00:33:57,319
Yours has orange,

671
00:33:57,480 --> 00:33:59,599
hawthorn, poria and red dates.

672
00:33:59,759 --> 00:34:00,480
Good for your energy.

673
00:34:01,640 --> 00:34:02,680
The grape flavor is strong.

674
00:34:02,880 --> 00:34:04,240
It's sweet even without sugar.

675
00:34:07,559 --> 00:34:08,280
Tastes great.

676
00:34:20,280 --> 00:34:20,800
Wenwen.

677
00:34:22,119 --> 00:34:22,639
Ma'am.

678
00:34:25,199 --> 00:34:26,000
Be quick.

679
00:34:26,000 --> 00:34:27,079
Find the old lady's phone!

680
00:34:54,159 --> 00:34:54,960
Wenwen?

681
00:34:56,679 --> 00:34:57,519
Fan Meijuan?

682
00:35:00,199 --> 00:35:01,039
Do you have a key?

683
00:35:01,320 --> 00:35:01,840
I do.

684
00:35:05,360 --> 00:35:05,920
This one.

685
00:35:09,719 --> 00:35:10,639
Wenwen?

686
00:35:12,400 --> 00:35:13,199
Wenwen?

687
00:35:18,400 --> 00:35:19,280
Fan Meijuan?

688
00:35:21,440 --> 00:35:23,119
That's strange. Nobody's home.

689
00:35:23,880 --> 00:35:24,880
Maybe they went out.

690
00:35:25,519 --> 00:35:27,719
The soup won't taste good
once it's cold.

691
00:35:28,280 --> 00:35:29,599
I'll call her.

692
00:35:42,960 --> 00:35:43,639
Hello?

693
00:35:45,679 --> 00:35:47,440
Hello.

694
00:35:47,679 --> 00:35:48,639
Who is this?

695
00:35:48,920 --> 00:35:50,239
I'm Tongtong.

696
00:35:51,559 --> 00:35:53,440
I'm her brother. My name's Boluo.

697
00:35:53,559 --> 00:35:54,920
How did you

698
00:35:54,920 --> 00:35:56,000
get this phone?

699
00:35:56,199 --> 00:35:57,119
At the grass field!

700
00:35:57,480 --> 00:35:59,159
I saw this phone first!

701
00:35:59,159 --> 00:36:00,679
No, I heard it first!

702
00:36:00,679 --> 00:36:02,159
No, it's me!

703
00:36:02,239 --> 00:36:03,559
No, it's me!

704
00:36:03,599 --> 00:36:04,920
I said this phone

705
00:36:05,079 --> 00:36:06,159
looked like my grandma's.

706
00:36:06,159 --> 00:36:07,039
Kids, stop fighting.

707
00:36:07,239 --> 00:36:08,360
Can you tell me

708
00:36:08,639 --> 00:36:10,239
where you are?

709
00:36:10,239 --> 00:36:11,159
I found it first!

710
00:36:11,199 --> 00:36:12,440
No, I heard it first!

711
00:36:12,480 --> 00:36:13,360
Me!

712
00:36:13,360 --> 00:36:15,480
There, there. Good kids.

713
00:36:15,599 --> 00:36:16,599
Tell me,

714
00:36:16,639 --> 00:36:18,079
where are you now?

715
00:36:18,199 --> 00:36:19,320
Forest Land.

716
00:36:19,760 --> 00:36:21,880
No. Forest Peninsula.

717
00:36:22,079 --> 00:36:23,519
We are at Forest Peninsula.

718
00:36:23,840 --> 00:36:25,079
Right below my apartment.

719
00:36:25,559 --> 00:36:26,960
Forest Peninsula. Forest Peninsula.

720
00:36:27,239 --> 00:36:28,519
Isn't that in Songshan District?

721
00:36:28,719 --> 00:36:29,960
How'd they get out there?

722
00:36:30,119 --> 00:36:31,760
Hello? Kids,

723
00:36:32,079 --> 00:36:32,880
this phone belongs

724
00:36:32,880 --> 00:36:34,320
to an old lady.

725
00:36:34,679 --> 00:36:35,719
Look around.

726
00:36:35,719 --> 00:36:37,519
Do you see any old lady nearby?

727
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:40,639
No.

728
00:36:41,679 --> 00:36:42,679
Take another look.

729
00:36:43,159 --> 00:36:44,440
Is there

730
00:36:44,440 --> 00:36:45,199
a young girl

731
00:36:45,400 --> 00:36:46,440
with big, round eyes

732
00:36:46,519 --> 00:36:47,639
and her hair in braids?

733
00:36:48,119 --> 00:36:49,480
A very pretty girl.

734
00:36:49,679 --> 00:36:52,280
No.

735
00:37:12,119 --> 00:37:13,639
(Mom)
♪Work hard and make money♪

736
00:37:13,760 --> 00:37:15,079
♪I want to get rich♪

737
00:37:18,199 --> 00:37:19,159
We...

738
00:37:19,280 --> 00:37:20,920
We've thought it over.

739
00:37:21,039 --> 00:37:22,679
We handled it badly last time.

740
00:37:22,760 --> 00:37:24,119
We've changed.

741
00:37:24,239 --> 00:37:25,800
We'll give you all the money
and the house.

742
00:37:25,880 --> 00:37:26,880
Everything back to you.

743
00:37:29,480 --> 00:37:30,159
I'm sorry.

744
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:32,599
Mom?

745
00:37:33,639 --> 00:37:35,199
Have you kept calling?

746
00:37:36,920 --> 00:37:38,280
Some kids found it.

747
00:37:38,840 --> 00:37:39,719
What kids?

748
00:37:41,199 --> 00:37:42,239
In Songshan District?

749
00:37:44,119 --> 00:37:45,039
We're coming now.

750
00:37:46,239 --> 00:37:46,800
Sorry.

751
00:37:46,920 --> 00:37:47,320
Very sorry.

752
00:37:47,320 --> 00:37:48,639
Let's talk another time.

753
00:38:04,800 --> 00:38:05,440
Yitong?

754
00:38:05,519 --> 00:38:06,360
Jiajia, where are you?

755
00:38:07,079 --> 00:38:08,440
Just got off work.

756
00:38:08,480 --> 00:38:08,960
What's wrong?

757
00:38:09,320 --> 00:38:10,800
Come to my place right now.

758
00:38:11,199 --> 00:38:11,880
Something happened.

759
00:38:11,880 --> 00:38:12,960
I'm freaking out.

760
00:38:14,159 --> 00:38:15,400
Okay, okay.

761
00:38:15,559 --> 00:38:16,159
What happened?

762
00:38:16,199 --> 00:38:16,880
Talk to you later.

763
00:38:17,000 --> 00:38:18,280
Don't worry. I'm on my way.

764
00:38:18,400 --> 00:38:18,800
Okay.

765
00:38:34,719 --> 00:38:35,679
What's wrong? Why the rush?

766
00:38:35,760 --> 00:38:36,840
My mom and Wenwen are missing.

767
00:38:37,880 --> 00:38:38,480
Missing?

768
00:38:40,000 --> 00:38:41,000
What do you mean?

769
00:38:43,280 --> 00:38:43,840
Mom.

770
00:38:44,800 --> 00:38:45,679
When did you notice?

771
00:38:46,320 --> 00:38:47,159
My parents got home

772
00:38:47,159 --> 00:38:47,920
around 5:30 pm,

773
00:38:47,920 --> 00:38:48,719
Wenwen wasn't there.

774
00:38:49,079 --> 00:38:49,760
Did you call them?

775
00:38:49,840 --> 00:38:50,400
Yes.

776
00:38:50,400 --> 00:38:50,960
My mom's phone

777
00:38:50,960 --> 00:38:51,880
was ringing in the bushes

778
00:38:51,880 --> 00:38:53,199
at Forest Peninsula.

779
00:38:53,639 --> 00:38:54,920
Yu Ming's parents
are looking for it now.

780
00:38:56,199 --> 00:38:57,400
What about Jiang Juan?

781
00:38:57,480 --> 00:38:58,199
I called.

782
00:38:58,199 --> 00:38:59,840
Can't get through.

783
00:38:59,840 --> 00:39:00,519
No one picks up.

784
00:39:00,519 --> 00:39:01,920
Don't panic.

785
00:39:01,920 --> 00:39:02,880
Wenwen's smart.

786
00:39:02,880 --> 00:39:03,679
Maybe she just

787
00:39:03,679 --> 00:39:04,760
took Grandma out somewhere.

788
00:39:04,800 --> 00:39:05,400
Out somewhere?

789
00:39:05,400 --> 00:39:06,840
Why was the phone in the bushes?

790
00:39:06,840 --> 00:39:07,880
Something's wrong.

791
00:39:08,159 --> 00:39:08,800
Call the cops.

792
00:39:09,039 --> 00:39:09,599
No.

793
00:39:09,920 --> 00:39:10,440
Why not?

794
00:39:10,679 --> 00:39:12,079
Is it about that money?

795
00:39:12,599 --> 00:39:13,280
We can't just wait here.

796
00:39:13,280 --> 00:39:13,960
Let's go find them.

797
00:39:14,239 --> 00:39:15,159
No. Tell me the truth.

798
00:39:15,239 --> 00:39:15,840
Is it related?

799
00:39:15,960 --> 00:39:16,559
This is different.

800
00:39:16,559 --> 00:39:17,039
Here's the thing.

801
00:39:17,039 --> 00:39:17,679
No one knows

802
00:39:17,679 --> 00:39:18,880
where that 60 million came from.

803
00:39:19,039 --> 00:39:19,480
Besides,

804
00:39:19,599 --> 00:39:21,000
if this really is kidnapping,

805
00:39:21,360 --> 00:39:22,519
and the kidnappers find out

806
00:39:22,519 --> 00:39:23,159
we called the police,

807
00:39:23,159 --> 00:39:24,199
they might kill Wenwen.

808
00:39:24,199 --> 00:39:25,000
That would be a disaster.

809
00:39:25,039 --> 00:39:26,199
Don't scare yourself like that.

810
00:39:26,199 --> 00:39:26,559
Alright?

811
00:39:26,599 --> 00:39:27,199
Maybe she just

812
00:39:27,199 --> 00:39:28,119
lost track of time.

813
00:39:28,320 --> 00:39:29,119
Tomorrow's Saturday.

814
00:39:29,119 --> 00:39:30,159
It's normal for her

815
00:39:30,159 --> 00:39:30,800
to be out longer.

816
00:39:32,400 --> 00:39:32,960
Go check the footage.

817
00:39:33,119 --> 00:39:33,719
I'll go with you.

818
00:39:35,320 --> 00:39:36,199
Jiajia, stay here.

819
00:39:36,199 --> 00:39:37,079
In case my mom comes back,

820
00:39:37,079 --> 00:39:38,039
call me, okay?

821
00:39:38,159 --> 00:39:38,599
Okay.

822
00:39:44,039 --> 00:39:44,679
Sorry.

823
00:39:45,199 --> 00:39:46,320
The number you have dialed

824
00:39:46,360 --> 00:39:47,639
cannot be reached at this time.

825
00:39:48,480 --> 00:39:49,800
Please try again later.

826
00:39:50,800 --> 00:39:51,440
Sorry.

827
00:39:52,079 --> 00:39:53,599
The number you have dialed...

828
00:39:53,679 --> 00:39:54,800
That camera's been dead for ages.

829
00:39:54,800 --> 00:39:56,039
It doesn't catch anything.

830
00:39:56,880 --> 00:39:58,440
But I remember there were two.

831
00:39:58,760 --> 00:39:59,760
Forget two.

832
00:39:59,760 --> 00:40:00,840
One by the back gate too.

833
00:40:00,840 --> 00:40:02,039
Three in total.

834
00:40:02,280 --> 00:40:03,519
They've all been broken for years.

835
00:40:03,519 --> 00:40:05,760
Those old rundown blocks,

836
00:40:05,760 --> 00:40:07,599
old rundown buildings,

837
00:40:07,719 --> 00:40:09,239
We can barely collect the property fees.

838
00:40:09,440 --> 00:40:10,960
Nobody bothers fixing the cameras.

839
00:40:11,119 --> 00:40:11,760
Come look.

840
00:40:12,159 --> 00:40:14,199
Covered in dust. What can they capture?

841
00:40:14,199 --> 00:40:15,559
Nothing. Absolutely nothing.

842
00:40:15,960 --> 00:40:16,360
Bomb!

843
00:40:17,719 --> 00:40:18,199
Pass.

844
00:40:20,119 --> 00:40:20,719
One this.

845
00:40:21,360 --> 00:40:22,000
Wenwen!

846
00:40:23,920 --> 00:40:24,480
Wenwen!

847
00:40:27,360 --> 00:40:28,079
Ms. Fan!

848
00:40:30,039 --> 00:40:30,719
Wenwen!

849
00:40:32,199 --> 00:40:32,880
Wenwen!

850
00:40:34,960 --> 00:40:35,480
Yu Ming.

851
00:40:35,559 --> 00:40:36,079
Wu.

852
00:40:36,079 --> 00:40:37,039
My daughter and mother-in-law

853
00:40:37,039 --> 00:40:38,119
went missing around Forest Peninsula.

854
00:40:38,119 --> 00:40:39,199
Please help me look for them.

855
00:40:39,840 --> 00:40:41,039
Don't panic.

856
00:40:41,320 --> 00:40:42,320
Forest Peninsula, right?

857
00:40:42,360 --> 00:40:43,639
I'll get people on it.

858
00:40:44,199 --> 00:40:45,000
Hello, Ouyang Qing.

859
00:40:45,159 --> 00:40:46,400
Wenwen and Ms. Fan are missing.

860
00:40:46,519 --> 00:40:47,320
Where they disappeared

861
00:40:47,320 --> 00:40:48,239
is not far from your school.

862
00:40:48,280 --> 00:40:48,960
Get your friends

863
00:40:48,960 --> 00:40:49,760
and classmates together

864
00:40:49,760 --> 00:40:50,719
and go look for them.

865
00:40:50,719 --> 00:40:51,719
I'll send you their photos.

866
00:40:52,119 --> 00:40:53,000
Could you help me

867
00:40:53,000 --> 00:40:53,840
check today's

868
00:40:53,840 --> 00:40:54,880
footage?

869
00:40:54,880 --> 00:40:55,360
What happened?

870
00:40:55,440 --> 00:40:56,559
My mother-in-law

871
00:40:56,559 --> 00:40:57,599
and my daughter are missing.

872
00:40:58,119 --> 00:40:59,159
When was it?

873
00:40:59,320 --> 00:40:59,800
This afternoon.

874
00:40:59,920 --> 00:41:01,079
Yeah, this afternoon.

875
00:41:01,079 --> 00:41:02,360
Just show me the afternoon footage.

876
00:41:16,519 --> 00:41:18,119
♪Work hard and make money♪

877
00:41:18,239 --> 00:41:19,679
♪I want to get rich♪

878
00:41:22,159 --> 00:41:22,719
Mom.

879
00:41:22,920 --> 00:41:23,840
Is Wenwen home?

880
00:41:24,199 --> 00:41:25,159
Not yet.

881
00:41:25,480 --> 00:41:26,639
Stay at Forest Peninsula.

882
00:41:26,639 --> 00:41:27,559
I'm coming right away.

883
00:41:58,719 --> 00:41:59,639
Grandma.

884
00:42:00,320 --> 00:42:01,119
They are awake.

885
00:42:01,199 --> 00:42:01,960
My helmet! Be quick!

886
00:42:02,320 --> 00:42:03,679
Not enough dosage.

887
00:42:05,800 --> 00:42:06,639
Give me more energy?

888
00:42:07,519 --> 00:42:09,000
Hawthorn, red dates,

889
00:42:10,280 --> 00:42:11,039
poria.

890
00:42:11,480 --> 00:42:12,840
You drugged us!

891
00:42:13,760 --> 00:42:14,880
You heartless thing!

892
00:42:16,679 --> 00:42:17,599
I get it now.

893
00:42:18,719 --> 00:42:19,519
I get it now.

894
00:42:19,840 --> 00:42:21,679
You got close to me

895
00:42:22,039 --> 00:42:23,719
in order to kill me?

896
00:42:23,920 --> 00:42:24,920
No need to be harsh,

897
00:42:24,920 --> 00:42:25,480
old lady.

898
00:42:26,159 --> 00:42:27,199
It's your own fault

899
00:42:27,599 --> 00:42:28,239
for being so naive.

900
00:42:28,239 --> 00:42:29,559
A few tears, and you bought it.

901
00:42:31,280 --> 00:42:31,960
Behave!

902
00:42:32,079 --> 00:42:32,840
I want to go home!

903
00:42:32,840 --> 00:42:33,480
I'll beat you!

904
00:42:33,480 --> 00:42:34,440
Wenwen, don't move.

905
00:42:34,519 --> 00:42:35,079
Wenwen.

906
00:42:35,440 --> 00:42:36,119
Don't move.

907
00:42:36,440 --> 00:42:37,400
Don't move. Listen.

908
00:42:37,800 --> 00:42:38,679
You wretch!

909
00:42:39,360 --> 00:42:40,639
Driving a car

910
00:42:41,239 --> 00:42:42,519
with a helmet on?

911
00:42:42,679 --> 00:42:44,280
- It's all fake.
- I'll beat you!

912
00:42:44,320 --> 00:42:45,199
I want to go home.

913
00:42:45,199 --> 00:42:46,199
Your daughter? Fake.

914
00:42:46,280 --> 00:42:47,639
Your husband hitting you?

915
00:42:47,639 --> 00:42:48,519
Fake too.

916
00:42:48,679 --> 00:42:50,920
You evil woman! Jiang!

917
00:42:51,159 --> 00:42:52,199
Don't move!

918
00:42:55,719 --> 00:42:57,199
You curse like you're singing.

919
00:42:57,400 --> 00:42:58,239
How interesting.

920
00:42:58,239 --> 00:42:58,960
Don't move.

921
00:42:59,280 --> 00:43:00,360
Don't move. Be good.

922
00:43:05,080 --> 00:43:07,880
(Next Episode)

923
00:43:08,079 --> 00:43:09,000
(Actor, Gu Jiacheng)
I'm Gu Jiacheng.

924
00:43:09,079 --> 00:43:11,079
(Actor, Gu Jiacheng)
I invite you to watch Wonder Wall.

925
00:43:12,400 --> 00:43:13,599
15 million each.

926
00:43:13,679 --> 00:43:14,760
30 million for both.

927
00:43:14,840 --> 00:43:16,159
Get the money ready. Wait for my call.

928
00:43:16,320 --> 00:43:16,800
How much do they want?

929
00:43:16,880 --> 00:43:17,559
30 million.

930
00:43:17,679 --> 00:43:18,719
Whatever they ask, do it.

931
00:43:19,159 --> 00:43:21,000
That is Zihan's school money.

932
00:43:21,360 --> 00:43:22,519
Whatever happened, she is my niece.

933
00:43:22,519 --> 00:43:23,440
How can I ignore this?

934
00:43:23,719 --> 00:43:24,880
- Fan Meijuan!
- Wenwen!

935
00:43:25,400 --> 00:43:25,960
Wenwen!

936
00:43:26,159 --> 00:43:26,880
Wenwen!

937
00:43:27,480 --> 00:43:28,199
Where is my 30 million?

938
00:43:28,400 --> 00:43:29,400
There are two different groups.

939
00:43:29,400 --> 00:43:30,360
This one never got the money.

940
00:43:30,360 --> 00:43:32,360
They are not the same people.

941
00:43:32,840 --> 00:43:33,719
They don't want to pay.

942
00:43:33,840 --> 00:43:34,559
They are just messing with us.

943
00:43:34,679 --> 00:43:35,960
Time to show them some blood.

944
00:43:55,610 --> 00:44:02,620
♪The road ahead is still so long
Where have you gone?♪

945
00:44:04,180 --> 00:44:11,340
♪Under the blazing sun
I keep heading north♪

946
00:44:12,760 --> 00:44:20,220
♪To those who pass me by
You don't have to look at me♪

947
00:44:21,360 --> 00:44:28,640
♪Just keep walking your own way
I'll manage on my own♪

948
00:44:31,630 --> 00:44:35,230
♪Is the rain falling hard?♪

949
00:44:35,870 --> 00:44:39,000
♪Is there someone
to hold an umbrella for you?♪

950
00:44:40,160 --> 00:44:44,940
♪The wind has blown
the numbers off the signs♪

951
00:44:44,940 --> 00:44:47,930
♪Where am I supposed to go?♪

952
00:44:48,730 --> 00:44:52,250
♪Can I change my mind?♪

953
00:44:53,010 --> 00:44:56,240
♪How do I go on without you?♪

954
00:44:57,550 --> 00:45:02,080
♪When will this
endless rain finally stop?♪

955
00:45:02,080 --> 00:45:04,780
♪Then I'll wait for you♪

956
00:45:04,780 --> 00:45:08,780
♪Please don't leave me waiting♪

